
[1]chaperon

   CHAPERON, n. A hood or cap worn by the knights of the garter in their
   habits. It was anciently worn by men, women, nobles and populace;
   afterwards appropriated to doctors and licentiates in colleges. The
   name then passed to certain devices placed on the foreheads of horses
   which drew the herse in pompous funerals.
